summary: [Spoilers] So I am just starting season 7 and I was thinking about something and wanted to see what you guys think.
title: [Spoilers] So I am just starting season 7 and I was thinking about something and wanted to see what you guys think.
body:
So I was thinking about Ned Stark and how hard it must have been for him to tarnish his reputation to protect Jon.

I mean all of the sacrifices that were made and then I realized that none of them will ever know the truth.

Ned lies and tells Catelyn that he cheated and had a bastard son, Catelyn hates Jon and wanted Ned to get rid of him because she couldn’t stand the sight of Jon, but Ned never did.

So Catelyn died and lived most of her life thinking that her husband was a cheater and the Honorable Ned Stark had to tarnish his reputation to protect Jon.

To top it all off, poor Jon had to live his entire life believing he was a bastard and wasn’t as good as the rest of the Starks. Jon’s adopted mother hated him and Sansa hated him as well.

I’m just starting season 7 but I started to think about all of that and I felt so bad. Ned will never get to clear his name, Catelyn will never know Jon wasn’t a bastard and Ned never cheated.

The only good that came out of it was that Ned really did love Jon and tried to treat him the same as any of his other children. Jon was well educated and was able to learn how to use a sword with Robb and thankfully none of his other siblings hated him like Sansa did.



Source: https://ift.tt/2O6DNOV
